						<summary>

						<p>States that <hi rend="bold">Malli-Dēsaṭi</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Prōli-Dēsaṭi</hi> who is described as lord of Kallaṟti-vishaya and the <hi rend="bold">Tumbūru-nāṇḍu</hi> and as a worshipper of the feet of <hi rend="bold">Jōti-Siddhavaṭṭēsvara,</hi> gave 25 cows for a perpetual lamp in the temple of Mallīśvara of <hi rend="bold">Bejavāḍa.</hi></p>						

